@DateTime.UtcNow.ToString("yyyy-MM-dd") is evaluated on the server 
when the page is rendered and prints the UTC date in the format YYYY-MM-DD.

Important: this is the render time. If a client loads the page 
later, this value does not auto-update.

@version outputs the version variable set earlier.

Server-side vs client-side

Everything you see with @... or in @{ ... } is executed on the server 
before HTML is sent to the browser. The browser receives plain 
HTML, CSS and JS — it does not run the C# code.

Small gotchas & details

Assembly.GetEntryAssembly() can be null in some hosting scenarios 
(e.g., certain test runners or some IIS host contexts). Your 
code already handles null with the ?? "n/a".

The Version returned by GetName().Version is the assembly version 
(from AssemblyVersionAttribute). If you want a more friendly or 
custom version (like Semantic Version or commit hash), you may prefer:

AssemblyInformationalVersionAttribute 
(Assembly.GetEntryAssembly()?.GetCustomAttribute<AssemblyInformationalVersionAttribute>()?.InformationalVersion)

or System.Diagnostics.FileVersionInfo.GetVersionInfo(assembly.Location).ProductVersion

DateTime.UtcNow prints UTC — if you want the viewer’s local 
time, either show server local time (DateTime.Now) or render 
the UTC value and convert in JavaScript. For multi-timezone apps, 
showing UTC with a note is safer.

The mailto: address is hard-coded. For maintainability, you 
might want to pull contact info from configuration.

Suggested improvements / alternatives

Use informational version (more descriptive):

@using System.Reflection
@{
    var infoVersion = Assembly.GetEntryAssembly()?
        .GetCustomAttribute<AssemblyInformationalVersionAttribute>()?
        .InformationalVersion ?? "n/a";
}
App version: @infoVersion


Use FileVersionInfo if GetEntryAssembly() is null in your host:

@using System.Diagnostics;
@{
    var entry = Assembly.GetEntryAssembly();
    var version = entry != null
        ? FileVersionInfo.GetVersionInfo(entry.Location).ProductVersion
        : "n/a";
}


Make Last updated dynamic in browser (optional):
Render the UTC date and use a tiny JS snippet to convert to 
local time client-side if desired.

Use config for contact email:
Store email in appsettings.json and read via the controller 
or IConfiguration so you can change it without editing the view.

Localization: format dates using culture-specific formatting 
or IViewLocalizer if you’re localizing the app.
